es from how displaced people negotiate the kinds of safety and protection that are offered to (and withheld from) them. In so doing, he lays the framework for an original and compelling understanding of contemporary refugee subjectivity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGratitude. 0aRefuge in literature. 0aRefugeeszNorth America. 0aResentment. 0aResilience (Personality trait) 0aResilience (Personality trait). 0aSoutheast AsianszNorth America. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Refugees.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520397279zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520397279zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520397279/original  a978-3-11-079134-1 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131910-0 EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-SEWb2023